reform movements in Aotearoa.

3519
03:25:54.760 --> 03:25:58.030
The principle behind that movement was simple: communities

3520
03:25:58.070 --> 03:26:02.010
experiencing the harm should have a meaningful say in how alcohol

3521
03:26:02.070 --> 03:26:02.870
is regulated.

3522
03:26:03.710 --> 03:26:06.610
That principle remains just as relevant today as it was

3523
03:26:06.670 --> 03:26:10.610
then. One of the reasons we're concerned about this bill is that it appears

3524
03:26:10.630 --> 03:26:12.350
to move us away from that principle.

3525
03:26:13.350 --> 03:26:16.550
At a time when communities are carrying the consequences of

3526
03:26:16.630 --> 03:26:20.349
alcohol-related harm, several provisions within the bill reduce

3527
03:26:20.430 --> 03:26:24.110
opportunities for communities to influence the decisions that affect them.

3528
03:26:25.350 --> 03:26:27.890
Tena koutou. Ko Jamie Hutana ahau.

3529
03:26:28.470 --> 03:26:30.710
He mokopuna o Porourangi me Kahungunu.

3530
03:26:31.890 --> 03:26:34.950
For 25 years, I've worked as a police officer in Te Tairawhiti.

3531
03:26:35.950 --> 03:26:39.550
During that time, I've attended numerous incidents where alcohol was a contributing

3532
03:26:39.630 --> 03:26:40.090
factor.

3533
03:26:41.030 --> 03:26:44.850
Family violence called out serious assaults, road crashes, mental health crisis,

3534
03:26:45.430 --> 03:26:46.630
and in some cases, death.

3535
03:26:48.130 --> 03:26:51.210
Over time, you begin to understand that alcohol harm is really confined to the

3536
03:26:51.290 --> 03:26:52.150
person drinking.

3537
03:26:52.990 --> 03:26:55.370
The people most affected are often the people around them.

3538
03:26:56.610 --> 03:27:00.470
Children who witness violence, partners who live in fear, parents who are trying to

3539
03:27:00.490 --> 03:27:01.460
hold families together,

3540
03:27:02.770 --> 03:27:06.730
friends, neighbors, wider whanau who are left dealing with the consequences long

3541
03:27:06.830 --> 03:27:09.590
after the incident itself is over.

3542
03:27:09.900 --> 03:27:13.820
What the stats don't capture is the cumulative impact that these incidents have

3543
03:27:13.870 --> 03:27:17.850
on communities. When alcohol contributes to harm, the effects

3544
03:27:17.890 --> 03:27:18.880
are felt

3545
03:27:19.930 --> 03:27:23.110
well beyond the immediate event. They affect

3546
03:27:23.130 --> 03:27:27.090
relationships, trust, well-being, and the sense of safety people feel in

3547
03:27:27.110 --> 03:27:28.730
their own homes and neighborhoods.

3548
03:27:31.250 --> 03:27:34.739
The other reality, as I witnessed over many years, was the impact on those

3549
03:27:34.770 --> 03:27:37.410
responding. Police officers, ambulance staff,

3550
03:27:38.410 --> 03:27:41.690
firefighters, emergency department workers regularly walk into

3551
03:27:41.750 --> 03:27:43.770
situations most people never see.

3552
03:27:44.990 --> 03:27:48.210
While we are trained to do that work, we are all still human.

3553
03:27:48.890 --> 03:27:50.550
We carry those experiences with us.

3554
03:27:51.970 --> 03:27:54.630
That is one of the reasons I feel strongly about prevention.

3555
03:27:55.050 --> 03:27:57.590
After 25 years on the frontline responding to harm,

3556
03:27:58.490 --> 03:28:02.030
I've come to understand that the real measure of success is not how well we

3557
03:28:02.070 --> 03:28:03.450
respond when things go wrong,

3558
03:28:04.350 --> 03:28:06.470
but how effectively we prevent them from happening at

3559
03:28:06.530 --> 03:28:10.174
allTime and again, I have seen the devastating

3560
03:28:10.254 --> 03:28:13.734
impact that alcohol-fueled harm can have on individuals,

3561
03:28:13.834 --> 03:28:15.234
whanau and communities.

3562
03:28:16.514 --> 03:28:20.454
Those experiences have convinced me that we must invest much more

3563
03:28:20.474 --> 03:28:24.384
in prevention if we are serious about creating safer and

3564
03:28:24.454 --> 03:28:25.434
healthier communities.

3565
03:28:26.894 --> 03:28:29.254
My own experience comes from a different perspective.

3566
03:28:29.864 --> 03:28:33.594
I led the news team at the Gisborne Herald for more than 20 years as editorial

3567
03:28:33.674 --> 03:28:37.634
manager, then editor. I've been on the Gisborne Chamber of Commerce executive board

3568
03:28:37.674 --> 03:28:41.434
for the past 20 years, and I've had various community leadership roles.

3569
03:28:41.474 --> 03:28:45.134
I'm a Gisborne district councillor now, as well as community strategist with Tane

3570
03:28:45.174 --> 03:28:45.354
Ora.

3571
03:28:46.414 --> 03:28:50.354
Journalism teaches you to look beyond individual events and pay attention

3572
03:28:50.394 --> 03:28:51.093
to patterns.

3573
03:28:51.994 --> 03:28:55.554
Over many years, I saw alcohol repeatedly sitting in the background

3574
03:28:55.974 --> 03:28:58.974
of some of the most difficult stories affecting our community.

3575
03:28:59.834 --> 03:29:02.294
Whether it is violence, road trauma,

3576
03:29:03.114 --> 03:29:06.974
crime, family harm, or broader social issues, alcohol

3577
03:29:07.014 --> 03:29:08.854
is often a big part of the picture.

3578
03:29:10.014 --> 03:29:13.974
At the same time, I also see communities doing extraordinary work to support one

3579
03:29:14.014 --> 03:29:17.714
another. I see schools, marae, sports clubs,

3580
03:29:17.994 --> 03:29:21.844
businesses, community organizations, and whanau stepping

3581
03:29:21.934 --> 03:29:25.434
up to create positive environments and opportunities for people.

3582
03:29:26.474 --> 03:29:29.894
One of the lessons I've taken from my experience is that strong

3583
